Privacy Policy
Introduction
MConverter OOD ("us", "we", or "our") operates the mconverter.eu website, MConverter mobile apps, and the MConverter API, collectively referred to as the Service.
This page informs you of our policies regarding the collection, use and disclosure of personal data when you use our Service and the choices you have associated with that data. We use your data only to provide and improve the Service.
Data Collection
We only collect the minimum amount of necessary data for providing and improving the Service.
By visiting and/or using our Service, your IP address will be logged, together with the user agent, HTTP referrer, and date and time of access.
If you contact us, we collect certain personally identifiable information, such as email and name, so that we can respond to enquiries.
When providing a file for conversion, we do not read or collect the file’s contents for reasons different from converting the file. We collect the number and types of errors when converting, as well as the original file size and name, for statistical purposes.
You may rate if you are satisfied with a conversion. The rating is collected for statistical purposes and to improve the Service.
If you create an MConverter account, we collect your email address. If you use an OAuth2 provider, we store a link to your profile picture.
If you choose to purchase or subscribe to a paid plan, we may need to collect some information, such as your email address, in order to verify the purchase and unlock your benefits. All financial transactions are handled by
Stripe
,
PayPro Global
for PayPal payments, or
Google Play
. We do not have access to your full debit/credit card number.
Usage of Data
We use your personal data only to provide and improve our Service. We do not make user profiles or anything similar.
Logging of your IP address is used for preventing abuse of our Service and for broad demographic analysis.
Handling of User Files
In the course of providing the service your files are transferred to and temporarily stored on our servers. We do not read, look into or mine any data from your files or their metadata. We do not make any copies of them. All file processing is done by machine and there is no human interaction with your files. Your files are automatically and irreversibly deleted from our servers at the latest after 36 hours, for conversions with an error. The files of successful conversions are deleted 4 hours after their completion. You can also manually initiate the deletion by clicking the DELETE NOW button.
Sharing of User Data
Your uploaded files will not be given out or sold to anyone. The same applies for the data associated with your MConverter account, if you have one. Any other personally identifiable information will not be given out or sold, either.
Retaining User Data
We will keep your personal data only for as long as it is necessary to provide you with our Services.
Your Rights
To exercise your rights, you can contact us from the LEGAL & CONTACT button in the main menu. Note that we might request you to provide additional information to enable us to identify your personal data and/or to verify your identity.
Request access to your data
You have the right to be given a copy of information held by us about you. We will provide the requested information to you within 30 calendar days of the receipt of a valid request as described above.
Request deletion of your data
You can request that we delete your data. Among other things, it may include your account and/or converted files. To request data deletion, click on LEGAL & CONTACT in the main menu, then on CONTACT US, enter your MConverter account's email address, select "I would like to... Delete my data (incl. account)" and submit the form.
Note that me way retain some information that is necessary to comply with legal obligations and for our legitimate business interests, such as fraud prevention.
You can also request the deletion of your files directly by clicking the DELETE NOW button after the conversion completes, which will be processed within a few seconds.
Security
We are committed to protect your personal data and your files. Our Service takes all necessary measures to keep your personal information and your files private and secure. Our staff are trained to properly handle your data.
MConverter maintains a secure IT environment and all security measures are constantly adjusted to technical progress. All transfers from and to our Service are SSL encrypted. Our servers are located in the European Union and have the appropriate measures in place to prevent unauthorised access, hacking.
Cookies
We store so-called cookies in order to be able to offer you a comprehensive range of functions and to make it easier to use our websites. Cookies are small files which are stored on your computer with the help of the internet browser. If you do not want to use cookies, you can prevent cookies from being stored on your computer using the corresponding settings on your internet browser. Please note that this may restrict the functional capability and the range of functions we offer.
Analytics
We may use Google Analytics to store information about how visitors use our Service so that we can make improvements and provide a better user experience. Google Analytics is a third-party information storage system by Google that records information about the pages you visit, the length of time you were on specific pages and the website in general, how you arrived at the site and what you clicked on. You can opt out of the usage of Google Analytics on this and all other websites with a browser extension.
Learn more about opting out
Advertisements
We may use Google AdSense, Google AdMob, and Setupad to display advertisements. These services may use cookies and other identifiers to serve ads based on the user's prior visits to our and/or other websites and apps. You can opt out of personalized advertising.
Learn more about Google ads
|
Opt out of Google ads personalization
|
More privacy settings (IAB CMP)
Cloudflare
We use Cloudflare to increase our security and handle attacks to our infrastructure. Furthermore, Cloudflare acts as a content delivery network to improve the reliability and speed of access to our Service. When accessing our Service, static content may be downloaded from a nearby Cloudflare server.
Learn more about Cloudflare's privacy and security practices
|
See Cloudflare's server locations
reCAPTCHA
We may use Google reCAPTCHA to identify and filter bots and SPAM. It is subject to the Google privacy policy.
Learn more about Google's privacy practices
Sentry.io
We use Sentry for error monitoring, so that we can diagnose and fix issues in our Service.
Learn more about Sentry's privacy practices
Fraud Prevention
We may use IPQualityScore and Proxycheck.io to detect virtual private network and proxy usage, as well as disposable email addresses. The detection is done using your IP address only. Your full email address is never shared.
See IPQualityScore's privacy policy
|
See Proxycheck's privacy policy
Email Campaigns
We may use HubSpot to create personalized email campaigns, if you consent. For this reason, your email address and name may be stored on HubSpot's servers.
See HubSpot's privacy policy
Customer Support
We may use HubSpot to process customer support inquiries through our contact forms and support email. For the purposes of being able to assist you, your email address, name, and message may be stored on HubSpot's servers.
See HubSpot's privacy policy
